text: Kamphaeng Phet is a town (thesaban mueang) in central Thailand, former capital of the Kamphaeng Phet Province. It covers the complete tambon Nai Mueang of the Mueang Kamphaeng Phet district. As of 2005 it has a population of 30,114. ==Climate== ==See also== * Mueang Kamphaeng Phet District * Kamphaeng Phet Province * Kamphaeng Phet Historical Park ==References== ==External links== * *http://www.kppcity.com Website of town (Thai only) Category:Populated places in Kamphaeng Phet Province Category:Cities and towns in Thailand
